<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 01 at 6:03PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong outflow winds will impact portions of Madison and
southeastern Beaverhead Counties through 630 PM MDT...
At 601 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of showers and
thunderstorms from 8 miles southwest of Alder, or 14 miles west of
Virginia City, extending south to near Monida, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Observed.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Ennis, Alder, Mcallister, Lakeview, Jeffers, Laurin,
Cameron, Raynolds Pass and Red Rock Pass.
This includes Highway 287 between mile markers 1  and 6 , and between
mile markers 1  and 65.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
